      • create

        public Csr create​(Csr csr)
        Description copied from interface: Csrs
        Creates a new certificate signing request (CSR) with selected extensions. A CSR is encrypted text that contains information about your organization (organization name, country, and so on), additional attributes as extensions, and your Web server's public key, which is a public certificate the is generated on the server that can be used to forward this request to a certificate authority (CA). A private key is also usually created at the same time as the CSR.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Specified by:
        create in interface Csrs

        Returns:

        public CertificateList importcsr​(java.lang.String csrId,
                                 TrustObjectData trustObjectData)
        Description copied from interface: Csrs
        Imports a certificate authority (CA)-signed certificate for a CSR. This action links the certificate to the private key created by the CSR. The pem_encoded string in the request body is the signed certificate provided by your CA in response to the CSR that you provide to them. After this operation you can delete the CSR.

      • selfsign

        public Certificate selfsign​(java.lang.String csrId,
                            long daysValid)
        Description copied from interface: Csrs
        Self-signs the previously generated CSR. This action is similar to the import certificate action, but instead of using a public certificate signed by a CA, the self_sign POST action uses a certificate that is signed with NSX's own private key. The maximum validity limit for non-CA certificates is 825 days, except for a value of 36,500 days, which should only be used for the cluster boot manager certificate. No limit is set for CA certificates.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Specified by:
        selfsign in interface Csrs
        Parameters:
        csrId - CSR this certificate is associated with (required)
        daysValid - Number of days the certificate will be valid, default 825 days (required)
        Returns:
        com.vmware.nsx.model.Certificate

      • selfsign

        public Certificate selfsign​(java.lang.String csrId,
                            long daysValid,
                            com.vmware.vapi.bindings.client.InvocationConfig invocationConfig)
        Description copied from interface: Csrs
        Self-signs the previously generated CSR. This action is similar to the import certificate action, but instead of using a public certificate signed by a CA, the self_sign POST action uses a certificate that is signed with NSX's own private key. The maximum validity limit for non-CA certificates is 825 days, except for a value of 36,500 days, which should only be used for the cluster boot manager certificate. No limit is set for CA certificates.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value. Use invocationConfig to specify configuration for this particular invocation.

The maximum validity limit for non-CA certificates is 825 days, except for a value of 36,500 days, which should only be used for the cluster boot manager certificate.
